      "text": [
        "هِ سَبْعَ مَرَّاتٍ فَإِذَا كَانَ أَمْراً جَسِيماً اِسْتَخَارَ اَللَّهَ مِائَةَ مَرَّةٍ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1554 - Hammad ibn Isa narrated from Najiyah, from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) that \"Whenever He (as) intended to purchase a servant, an animal, or a light matter, or something of little importance, he would perform istikhara (seek Allah’s (swt) guidance) seven times.\nBut if it was a serious matter, he would perform istikhara one hundred times”."
        ]
      }
    },
